    "individual_blog_7UKfT3": {
      "type": "individual-blog",
      "blocks": {
        "rich_text_GhprbG": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Heading",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>Which Metal is Best For Engagement and Wedding Rings</h1>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "follow_us_HatAtA": {
          "type": "follow_us",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Follow Us on"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_jmPYQq": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "1st Para",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>When people think about <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/engagement-rings\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">engagement rings</span></a> or <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/wedding-rings\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">wedding rings</span></a>, it’s usually the sparkle in the diamond they picture first. That center stone gets all the attention, but the metal underneath is just as important. </p><p>This band isn’t just jewelry, it’s something you’ll carry with you every single day. It should look good, feel right, and stand the test of time. The ring metal not only makes the foundation of the ring but also gives it a beautiful accent and charm. And with so many options - yellow gold, white gold, platinum, rose gold,, it helps to know what you’re actually putting on your finger.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_h7cyrE": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Yellow Gold: The Tried-and-True Classic",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Yellow Gold: The Tried-and-True Classic</h2>",
            "custom_id": "yellow"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_rwYXqc": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/YG.png",
            "text": "<p>From fairy tales to family heirlooms, yellow gold has been around forever, and it’s not going anywhere. That warm, rich tone is a classic, perfect for those with warmer skin tones.</p><p>You’ll usually find it in 14K, 18K. The higher the karat or the purity, the softer the metal. That means the 18K gold ring looks luxurious, but might show scratches faster, while 14K is tougher and better for daily wear.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "medium"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_aizqGY": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Yet, there’s something about that golden glow that feels so timeless! It’s elegant without trying. So choose the one that makes you feel a little more like yourself.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_KJNEWY": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "White Gold: Cool & Elegant",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>White Gold: Cool & Elegant</h2>",
            "custom_id": "white"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_MgzmmH": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/WG.png",
            "text": "<p>If you like a modern, classy and put-together look, white is the choice for you. It gets its shine from alloying pure gold with other white metals, such as nickel, palladium, or silver, to achieve its characteristic white color and strength. White gold is usually rhodium plated, giving it that icy, cool look. It pairs well with cooler skin tones, making you and your diamond shine brighter.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "adaptive"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_hHw8Ax": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Rose Gold: A Little Touch of Vintage",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Rose Gold: A Little Touch of Vintage</h2>",
            "custom_id": "rose"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_WcQxHk": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/RG.png",
            "text": "<p>Soft pink, kind of romantic, and a popular choice right now, rose gold feels like something you'd find in an old jewelry box, but still fits perfectly with today’s styles.</p><p>The color comes from copper mixed in with the gold. The copper is not just aesthetic but also strong. So not only does rose gold look different, it also holds up well over the years. Rose gold is versatile and pairs well with most skin tones, you can never go wrong with this one.</p>",
            "reverse_layout": false,
            "custom_id": "",
            "image_size_option": "adaptive"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_H4CLBW": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>However, in some years, it may deepen in tone slightly. Some people love that natural aging effect, it gives the ring character and personality.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_QY86RC": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Which One Should You Go For?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Which One Should You Go For?</h2><p><br/>Surrounded by irresistible elegance? Ask yourself these questions to figure out which one is the perfect choice for you:</p>",
            "custom_id": "which"
          }
        },
        "image_AfzNjw": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Question_about_Metal.png"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_DPKeq4": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<ul><li>Do you like warm tones or cool tones? Yellow gold is the best choice if you prefer warm tones, white gold is perfect for those who love cool tones, and rose gold pair well with most skin tones, so that would be your safest bet.</li><li>Do you need something tough-as-nails or soft and elegant? If you’re someone with a hands-on, active lifestyle, 14K gold is the ideal choice for you. If you are one who prefers luxury, then 18K is the perfect pick.</li><li>Do you want low maintenance, or are you okay with occasional touch-ups? While metals like white gold will need a bit of maintenance and upkeep, bands made with yellow gold will keep up with your active lifestyle for years to come.</li></ul><p><br/>And maybe most importantly: how does it feel on your hand? The feeling you get when you put on a potential engagement ring is the most important. All other details can be <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/pages/customized-jewelry\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Customized Diamond Jewelry\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">customized</span></a>, but the rush of happiness you get when you’ve found your ring, is the most important thing.</p><p>Lucira Jewelry’s collection covers the whole spectrum, from sleek white gold <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/solitaires\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lab Grown Diamond Solitaires\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">solitaires</span></a> to delicate rose gold <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/halo-engagement-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lab Grown Halo Diamond Engagement RIng\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">halos</span></a>. </p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        }
      },
